HEADWORD: Supraorbitar
<hw>Su`pra*or"bit*ar</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Situated
above the orbit of the eye.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Supraorbital point</b></col> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <cd>the
middle point of the supraorbital line, which is a line drawn across the
narrowest part of the forehead, separating the face from the cranium;
the ophryon.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suprapedal</ent>⟦br⟧
